text: Stig Ragnar Lindbäck (2 October 1937 – 14 March 1999) was a Swedish middle- distance runner. He competed in the 800 m and 1500 m events at the 1964 Olympics, but failed to reach the finals. Lindbäck won the national 800 m title in 1962. ==References== Category:1937 births Category:1999 deaths Category:Swedish male middle-distance runners Category:Olympic athletes of Sweden Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1964 Summer Olympics
